HEADWORD: callyciflorous
<hw>cal*lyc`i*flo"rous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>calyx</ets>, <ets>-ycis</ets>, calyx + <ets>flos</ets>,
<ets>floris</ets>, flower.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the
petals and stamens adnate to the calyx; -- applied to a subclass of
dicotyledonous plants in the system of the French botanist
<person>Candolle</person>.</def>⟦br⟧
